- I cannot be in position 4.

- I in position 3 (allowed).
- H (new letter), C (new letter), K (new letter).
- THICK uses five fresh letters (for us) except T and I which we know are present.

But let’s check:
- T is allowed in position 1 (since UNTIL had T in 3, and now we test 1).
- I is allowed in position 3 (since UNTIL had I in 4, now 3).

Thus THICK is valid.
